com.microsoft.windowsazure.services.blob.models

Class ListContainersResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.microsoft.windowsazure.services.blob.models.ListContainersResult

  • public class ListContainersResult
extends java.lang.Object
    A wrapper class for the response returned from a Blob Service REST API List Containers operation. This is returned by calls to implementations of BlobContract.listContainers() and BlobContract.listContainers(ListContainersOptions).

    See the List Containers documentation on MSDN for details of the underlying Blob Service REST API operation.

      • getMarker

        public java.lang.String getMarker()
        Gets the value of the marker that was used to specify the beginning of the container list to return with the request. This value is not set if a marker was not specified in the request.

        The List Containers operation returns a marker value in a NextMarker element if the container list returned is not complete. The marker value may then be used in a subsequent call to request the next set of container list items. The marker value is opaque to the client.

        Use the getNextMarker method to get the marker value to set on a ListContainersOptions instance using a call to ListContainersOptions.setMarker(String). Pass the ListContainersOptions instance as a parameter to a BlobContract.listContainers(ListContainersOptions) call to get the next portion of the container list.

        Returns:
        A String containing the marker used to specify the beginning of the container list returned, if any.

      • getMaxResults

        public int getMaxResults()
        Gets the maximum number of container list items to return that was specified in the request. The number of containers returned in a single response will not exceed this value. This value is not set if a maximum number was not specified in the request. If there are more containers that satisfy the request than this maximum value, the server will include a next marker value in the response, which can be used to get the remaining containers with a subsequent request.

        Use the getNextMarker method to get the marker value to set on a ListContainersOptions instance using a call to ListContainersOptions.setMarker(String). Pass the ListContainersOptions instance as a parameter to a BlobContract.listContainers(ListContainersOptions) call to get the next portion of the container list.

        Returns:
        The maximum number of container list items to return that was specified in the request, if any.
